Let $G$ be a graph with $n$ vertices such that $\Delta(G) \le \Delta$. For any positive integer $d$, there is some subgraph $H$ of $G$ such that:
\begin{enumerate}
    \item The degree of $H$ is $\le d$.
    \item The largest clique in $G - H$ has size $\le 16\ln(n) \cdot \frac{\Delta}{d} + 10$.
\end{enumerate}
